{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011NkwkoJrSs7HwzSSdW3aR3","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have the complete picture of the bug. Let me create a comprehensive summary document:\n\n## Summary of Bug Report\n\nI have identified the bug in the project info page where clicking expansion arrows (the `<details>` elements) in the Prompts section shows git diffs instead of file contents. Here are the findings:\n\n### Files Involved\n\n1. **Backend Handler:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n   - Lines 939-1025: `handleAPIProjectInfo()` function\n   - Lines 1027-1056: `handleAPIPromptDiff()` function\n\n2. **Frontend Template:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n   - Lines 98-121: `loadProjectInfo()` JavaScript function\n   - Lines 123-139: `toggleDiff()` JavaScript function\n\n3. **Styling:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n   - Lines 550-563: `.diff-block` styling for diff display\n\n### The Bug\n\nThe issue is in the interaction between the frontend and backend:\n\n**Frontend Problem (lines 100-115 in project_detail.html):**\n- The `<details>` elements are created with file paths as summaries\n- Inside each `<details>`, commit history entries are displayed (SHA, date, message)\n- Each commit entry is clickable via `toggleDiff(this)` function\n- The user expects to see the **file contents** when clicking the expansion arrow, but instead sees **git diffs**\n\n**Root Cause:**\nThe `<details>` element's native expand/collapse behavior is not wired to show the file contents. The only interactivity implemented is on individual commit entries (via `toggleDiff()`), which calls the `/api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff` endpoint (line 131) to show diffs.\n\n**What's Missing:**\nThere is **no endpoint or handler** to fetch the actual prompt file content. The backend only provides:\n1. `handleAPIProjectInfo()` - Returns file paths and git commit history\n2. `handleAPIPromptDiff()` - Returns git diffs for a specific commit\n\nThere is **no handler** to return the current file content of a prompt file.\n\n**Expected Behavior:**\nWhen users click the `<details>` expansion arrow, they should see the file contents of that prompt file, not a diff. The current commit history is useful as a secondary detail, but the primary interaction should display the file itself.\n\n### Recommended Fix\n\nYou need to:\n\n1. **Add a new backend endpoint** (e.g., `/api/projects/{name}/prompt-content`) that reads and returns the current content of a prompt file\n2. **Modify the frontend** to wire the `<details>` element's toggle event to fetch and display the file content\n3. **Keep the existing diff functionality** as a secondary feature on commit entries\n\n### File Locations (Absolute Paths)\n\n- Backend logic: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 939-1056)\n- Frontend UI: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (lines 89-139)\n- CSS: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` (lines 550-563)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a82c59560fd0ce38d (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 51095\ntool_uses: 16\nduration_ms: 21154</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"047d3608-205d-49ff-a46c-c3823d434eb4","uuid":"8dd5f6a9-ed2e-446a-8fd4-bdf477129a05","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to find the code responsible for displaying prompts in a \"project info page\" with expansion arrows. The bug is that clicking expansion arrows in the Prompts section shows git commits instead of file contents. \n\nSearch for:\n1. Any UI/TUI code related to \"prompts\" section display\n2. Code that handles expansion/collapse of prompts\n3. Code that reads prompt file contents for display\n4. Any code that might mistakenly show git commits instead of file contents\n\nLook in the entire codebase, especially in cmd/, internal/, and any TUI-related packages. Search for keywords like \"prompt\", \"expand\", \"collapse\", \"arrow\", \"info\", \"project info\", \"detail\", \"git log\", \"commit\".","agentId":"a82c59560fd0ce38d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have the complete picture of the bug. Let me create a comprehensive summary document:\n\n## Summary of Bug Report\n\nI have identified the bug in the project info page where clicking expansion arrows (the `<details>` elements) in the Prompts section shows git diffs instead of file contents. Here are the findings:\n\n### Files Involved\n\n1. **Backend Handler:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n   - Lines 939-1025: `handleAPIProjectInfo()` function\n   - Lines 1027-1056: `handleAPIPromptDiff()` function\n\n2. **Frontend Template:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n   - Lines 98-121: `loadProjectInfo()` JavaScript function\n   - Lines 123-139: `toggleDiff()` JavaScript function\n\n3. **Styling:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n   - Lines 550-563: `.diff-block` styling for diff display\n\n### The Bug\n\nThe issue is in the interaction between the frontend and backend:\n\n**Frontend Problem (lines 100-115 in project_detail.html):**\n- The `<details>` elements are created with file paths as summaries\n- Inside each `<details>`, commit history entries are displayed (SHA, date, message)\n- Each commit entry is clickable via `toggleDiff(this)` function\n- The user expects to see the **file contents** when clicking the expansion arrow, but instead sees **git diffs**\n\n**Root Cause:**\nThe `<details>` element's native expand/collapse behavior is not wired to show the file contents. The only interactivity implemented is on individual commit entries (via `toggleDiff()`), which calls the `/api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff` endpoint (line 131) to show diffs.\n\n**What's Missing:**\nThere is **no endpoint or handler** to fetch the actual prompt file content. The backend only provides:\n1. `handleAPIProjectInfo()` - Returns file paths and git commit history\n2. `handleAPIPromptDiff()` - Returns git diffs for a specific commit\n\nThere is **no handler** to return the current file content of a prompt file.\n\n**Expected Behavior:**\nWhen users click the `<details>` expansion arrow, they should see the file contents of that prompt file, not a diff. The current commit history is useful as a secondary detail, but the primary interaction should display the file itself.\n\n### Recommended Fix\n\nYou need to:\n\n1. **Add a new backend endpoint** (e.g., `/api/projects/{name}/prompt-content`) that reads and returns the current content of a prompt file\n2. **Modify the frontend** to wire the `<details>` element's toggle event to fetch and display the file content\n3. **Keep the existing diff functionality** as a secondary feature on commit entries\n\n### File Locations (Absolute Paths)\n\n- Backend logic: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 939-1056)\n- Frontend UI: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (lines 89-139)\n- CSS: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` (lines 550-563)"}],"totalDurationMs":21154,"totalTokens":51095,"totalToolUseCount":16,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":922,"cache_read_input_tokens":49409,"output_tokens":761,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":922},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
